&ldquo;Do you want anything from the coffee shop, Julia?&rdquo;
&ldquo;No, I&rsquo;m fine thanks, Coco.&rdquo;
Coco put on her jacket and slung her bag around her shoulder as she headed for the door. Julia and Coco shared a small room together. Just two desks amid a sea of folders and loose paper.
As she opened and closed the office door behind her, Coco smiled at the logo printed on the glass which read, I should Coco.
